    {
      "type": "explanation",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "Initials & Aspiration"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "In Cantonese, many consonants come in pairs: <strong>Unaspirated</strong> (no air) and <strong>Aspirated</strong> (a puff of air)."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Try this: Hold your hand in front of your mouth. When you say an 'aspirated' sound, you should feel a strong burst of air!"
        },
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "The B and P Pair"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "In Jyutping, 'b' is like the 'p' in 'spin' (no air), while 'p' is like the 'p' in 'pin' (lots of air)."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "八",
          "romanization": "baat3",
          "translation": "Eight"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "拍",
          "romanization": "paak3",
          "translation": "Clap"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "reading",
      "exerciseId": "1.3.2"
    },
    {
      "type": "unscramble",
      "exerciseId": "1.3.3"
    },
    {
      "type": "explanation",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "The D and T Pair"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Similar to B and P, 'd' is unaspirated (like 't' in 'stop') and 't' is aspirated (like 't' in 'top')."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "大",
          "romanization": "daai6",
          "translation": "Big"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "太",
          "romanization": "taai3",
          "translation": "Too / Extremely"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "reading",
      "exerciseId": "1.3.4"
    },
    {
      "type": "unscramble",
      "exerciseId": "1.3.5"
    },
    {
      "type": "explanation",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "The G and K Pair"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "'g' is unaspirated (like 'k' in 'skill') and 'k' is aspirated (like 'k' in 'kill')."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "加",
          "romanization": "gaa1",
          "translation": "Add"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "各",
          "romanization": "gok3",
          "translation": "Each"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "卡",
          "romanization": "kaa1",
          "translation": "Card"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "reading",
      "exerciseId": "1.3.6"
    },
